I don’t remember BBI stopping the Ministry of Health, for instance, from using their Covid-19 response funds prudently.I don’t either remember BBI stopping Kenyans from observing Covid-19 prevention protocols, such as wearing of face masks. Imagine a situation where the famous Handshake never happened. Peace is such a tranquiliser, often creating complacency and lethargy among feeble minds.
We seem to have forgotten how the country was increasingly becoming ungovernable. Truly, we never know what we have till we lose it. But that’s beside the point.



