Honestly, I don’t remember BBI stopping the Ministry of Health, for instance, from using their Covid-19 response funds prudently. I don’t either remember BBI stopping Kenyans from observing Covid-19 prevention protocols, such as wearing of face masks.
May be the resources spent towards it, however, unspecified, should have been used to bribe them into compliance. BBI hasn’t either stopped government ministries from executing their functions, hence serving the public accordingly.
2022 General Election
And this is where my dalliance with politicians ends. While some sound unreasonably rigid and intolerant to voices of dissent, others pass as opportunists who capitalize on the plight and ignorance of citizens to advance their selfish agenda.



